  "prompt": "What is Nuclear Insurance Pool?",
  "response": "A Nuclear Insurance Pool is a collaborative arrangement among multiple insurance companies to provide coverage for risks associated with nuclear power plants and related facilities. Here are key details about Nuclear Insurance Pools:\n\n1. Purpose\n- Provides insurance coverage for nuclear-related risks\n- Spreads potential financial liability across multiple insurers\n- Helps manage high-risk and potentially catastrophic scenarios\n\n2. Key Characteristics\n- Collective risk-sharing mechanism\n- Allows insurers to share complex and potentially large-scale risks\n- Provides comprehensive coverage for nuclear facilities\n\n3. Coverage Areas\n- Property damage\n- Third-party liability\n- Potential radiation-related incidents\n- Business interruption\n- Environmental cleanup costs\n\n4. Structure\n- Multiple insurance companies participate\n- Each member contributes a portion of the total risk\n- Typically managed by a central coordinating organization\n\n5. Benefits\n- Enables insurance for high-risk nuclear facilities\n- Reduces individual insurers' potential financial exposure\n- Provides more comprehensive coverage options\n\n6. International Examples\n- American Nuclear Insurers (ANI)\n- Nuclear Electric Insurance Limited (NEIL)\n- Various national and regional nuclear insurance pools\n\nThese pools play a crucial role in managing risks associated with nuclear energy infrastructure.",
